    <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
      This ProjektVPN system collects and makes public infornation about what public keys are registered in the system, when they were registered, how long they are paid up for, and what Bitcoin addresses received payments for each account.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>By coordinating this information with the public blockchain, it may be possible to identify account holders as such.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      This ProjektVPN system does not collect and cannot provide any information on what users are currently connected, or the sources, destinations, or content of traffic flowing through the VPN.
    </p>
    <h2>Code Availability</h2>
    <p>
      Of course, these privacy assertions are only valid if the system you are communicating with is running an unmodified ProjektVPN codebase, and is not running additional logging software. Since ProjektVPN is licensed under the AGPL, a server operator must publish any modifications that they have made to the code.
    </p>
